that soul in these unsocial woods , Where anguish muses , and where horror broods , From love's wild visionary wishes strayed , And sought to lose thy beauties in the shade , Faith dropped a smile , devotion lent her fire
me enraptured to the blessed abode

fond to save , To love's soft empire every wish betrayed
my laurels withering in the shade
these dark , cheerless , solitary caves , Death-breathing woods , and daily-opening graves , Misshapen rocks , wild images of woe , For ever howling to the deeps below

Her idol-beauties on each altar glare , And heaven much-injured has but half my prayer : No tears can drive her hence , no pangs control , For every object brings her to my soul

my lost soul thy brighter virtues feel , Warmed with thy hopes

when these black terrific scenes are over , And rebel nature chills the soul no more ; When on thy cheek the expiring roses fade , And thy last lustres darken in the shade ; When armed with quick varieties of pain , Or creeping dully slow from vein to vein , Pale death shall set my kindred spirit free , And these dead orbs forget to dote on thee ; Some pious friend , whose wild affections glow Like ours , in sad similitude of woe , Shall drop one tender , sympathising tear , Prepare the garland , and adorn the bier ; Our lifeless reliques in one tomb enshrine , And teach thy genial dust to mix with mine
creeping dully slow from vein to vein , Pale death
while , divinely purged from every stain , Our active souls shall climb the etherial plain
Mean while , divinely purged from every stain , Our active souls shall climb the etherial plain , To each bright cherub's purity aspire
no face the glooms of anguish wears , No uncle murders
